    <h1>
        Our Management Team</h1>
    <h3>
        Peter Mazonson, MD, MBA, Principal &amp; Co-Founder</h3>
    <p>
        Dr. Mazonson has over 25 years of experience developing successful health care software 
        and service companies. He has extensive experience in health care reimbursement and 
        health economics. Prior to co-founding ClearCost Health, he served as Vice President 
        of McKesson Corporation.  Dr. Mazonson came to McKesson from Mosaic Health Care, a 
        company he co-founded with Chris Santas that performed medical reimbursement consulting 
        and developed reimbursement software for physicians. Other previous positions include 
        President of Technology Assessment Group (an international outcomes research consulting 
        firm), Senior Vice President of the Lewin Group, and Senior Vice President of R2 Technology 
        (a software imaging company). Along with his work at ClearCost Health, Peter continues to 
        practice part-time as a general internist in San Jose, CA. He received his BA from Harvard 
        University, his MD from Dartmouth Medical School, and his MBA from Stanford.
    </p>        
    <h3>
        Chris Santas, MBA, Principal & Co-Founder</h3>
    <p>
        Chris has over 25 years of experience working with a broad range of health care companies, 
        including pharmaceutical and device manufacturers, pharmacy benefits managers, health 
        maintenance organizations, large insurance companies, and academic medical centers. 
        Prior to co-founding ClearCost Health, Chris served as Vice President of Reimbursement 
        and Health Economics for McKesson, where he spearheaded development of TotalView 
        reimbursement software and provided health economic and outcomes research consulting 
        services. Chris came to McKesson from Mosaic Health Care Consultants, another company 
        that he co-founded with Dr. Mazonson in 2003 focused on medical software development and 
        consulting. Chris has previously held management positions with R2 Technology, The Lewin 
        Group (Quintiles), Technology Assessment Group, and Deloitte & Touche. He received his 
        BA in Political Economy from UC Berkeley, and his MBA from Stanford.
    </p>
    <h3>
        Mark Agnew, Chief Marketing Officer</h3>
    <p>
        Mark leads sales and marketing for ClearCost Health. He brings over 25 years of 
        large employer HR and benefits consulting experience to the management team, having 
        been a Principal with Towers Perrin, Watson Wyatt and a Senior Vice President with 
        Fidelity Investments. Prior to joining ClearCost Health, Mark consulted with large 
        plan sponsors nationwide and founded BeneTweet, a wellness messaging service for 
        large plan sponsors using Facebook and Twitter. He received his BA in Economics from 
        Stanford University.
    </p>
    <h3>
        Cody Cargill, MBA, Senior Director of Business Development & Operations</h3>
    <p>
        Cody has a financial analysis background, focused mainly on the health care sector. 
        Prior to joining ClearCost Health, Cody worked at TA Associates, an $18 billion private 
        equity firm.  While there, he worked on investments such as Millennium Laboratories 
        (therapeutic drug testing), Alere Medical (disease management) and TwinMed (nursing home 
        supplies).  Cody began his career at Merrill Lynch, focused on M&A transactions within 
        the investment banking division.  He received his BA in Economics from Yale and his MBA from 
        Harvard.
    </p>
    <h3>
        Sujata Gidumal, Account Director
    </h3>
    <p>
        Sujata works closely with ClearCost Health clients to implement our services with maximum 
        engagement and savings for plan sponsors. Her background is in public relations and 
        marketing. Prior to ClearCost Health, Sujata worked in account management at Hunter 
        Public Relations in New York City. Sujata received her BA from Brown University
    </p>
    <h3>
        Bob Hart, Chief Technology Officer
    </h3>
    <p>
        Bob is a software development expert with more than 20 years of leadership experience 
        in health care information technology developing a wide range of applications including 
        voice/image processing, hospital and physician applications and large-scale data analytics 
        systems.  Before joining ClearCost Health, he served as CTO for Resolution Health, a 
        healthcare analytics company acquired by WellPoint.  Prior to Resolution Health, Bob held 
        leadership positions at SunGard, McKesson, and QuadraMed.  Bob received his BS in Computer 
        Engineering from the University of Texas and his MBA from Babson College. 
    </p>
    <h3>
        Syam Palakurthy, Senior Director of Product
    </h3>
    <p>
        Syam brings a diverse set of experience from his time at Bain & Company where he consulted 
        with multinational corporations in several industries, including Entertainment, Semiconductors, 
        Telecommunications, and Energy Utilities.  His consulting experience included working with the 
        human resources group of a Fortune 100 company.  He has also worked in Supply Chain Management 
        at Target Corp and Market Analysis at EnerNOC.  He received his BA in Engineering and Economics 
        from Dartmouth College.
    </p>
    <h3>
        Arthi Vijayaraghavan, MS, Senior Director of Data Management and Analytics
    </h3>
    <p>
        Arthi leads the data management and analytics functions at ClearCost Health. She has a background 
        in Health Economics and Reimbursement Strategy and has published several manuscripts in leading 
        journals.  Prior to joining ClearCost Health, Arthi held product and business development roles 
        at McKesson Corp.  She joined McKesson through the acquisition of Mosaic Healthcare Consultants.  
        Arthi began her career as a researcher at the Jules Stein Eye Institute at the UCLA School of 
        Medicine. She received her MS in Biomedical Engineering from UCLA and is currently pursuing her MBA 
        at the UC Berkeley Haas School of Business.
    </p>
